not private auto.

00:11:59.290 --> 00:12:00.820
But this is in
absolute terms, not

00:12:00.820 --> 00:12:03.370
in relative terms in
terms of mode share.

00:12:03.370 --> 00:12:10.500
If we look at recent
trends from 2004 to 2014,

00:12:10.500 --> 00:12:13.350
we see an increase in
public transportation

00:12:13.350 --> 00:12:15.900
that is quite high,
especially when you compare it

00:12:15.900 --> 00:12:18.160
to the population increase.

00:12:18.160 --> 00:12:21.810
And when you compare it to
the change in highway vehicle

00:12:21.810 --> 00:12:24.300
miles of travel in the
US at national level.

00:12:24.300 --> 00:12:27.600
So we see a 2% increase
in highway vehicle miles

00:12:27.600 --> 00:12:32.790
traveled and about 9%
increase in population

00:12:32.790 --> 00:12:36.810
and about 21% increase in
public transportation use.

00:12:36.810 --> 00:12:38.730
So it's been
especially recently.

00:12:38.730 --> 00:12:44.580
And you can see a dip due to the
most recent economic recession,

00:12:44.580 --> 00:12:47.280
but a pretty healthy
recovery after that.

00:12:47.280 --> 00:12:49.000
And part of what's
